  <summary date="2016-07-05T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">U.S. Wants to Compete for a World Expo Act

This bill expresses the sense of Congress that the United States should rejoin the Bureau of International Expositions (BIE) to promote public diplomacy, global branding, and tourism to the United States.

 The Department of State shall take necessary action within 90 days for the United States to rejoin the BIE.</summary>
